author: @wanseuujjang5901
text:
Momo's inclusion to TWICE is one controversial move by jyp, but for sure the risk paid off. As she said before, she doesn't cry as much now than she did during sixteen, but i feel like she still constantly thinks about sixteen and the "burden" she must have felt being the "special one" being handpicked by the agency. She has then worked so much to prove herself, and it is evident. Her vocals are improving, and it's undeniable that she is leading the dance and performance aura of TWICE for each consecutive comeback. And more so, she is recognized as one of the top female dancers in kpop. 

And then she had to go through this "dating scandal". Why is dating even a scandal? Think about it, the act of stalking is the real scandal, and shame on those whose can't do anything else than stalk celebrities. Momo deserves the world after all the efforts she did. And besides, she is dating probably the most trustworthy male idol in the industry. At least let us be supportive of her choices and her happiness, she doesn't deserve the hate.

We love you momo!! Fighting!! ğŸ‘
